Rich text and formatting in the terminal
Usage: rich [OPTIONS] <PATH,TEXT,URL, or '-'>
â”‚ -p --print Print console markup. See https://rich.readthedocs.io/en/latest/markup.html â”‚
â”‚ -u --rule Display a horizontal rule. â”‚
â”‚ -j --json Display as JSON. â”‚
â”‚ -m --markdown Display as markdown. â”‚
â”‚ --rst Display restructured text. â”‚
â”‚ --csv Display CSV as a table. â”‚
â”‚ --ipynb Display Jupyter notebook. â”‚
â”‚ --syntax Syntax highlighting. â”‚
â”‚ --inspect Inspect a python object. â”‚
â”‚ -h --head LINES Display first LINES of the file (requires --syntax or --csv). â”‚
â”‚ -t --tail LINES Display last LINES of the file (requires --syntax or --csv). â”‚
â”‚ -j --emoji Enable emoji code. e.g. :sparkle: â”‚
â”‚ -l --left Align to left. â”‚
â”‚ -r --right Align to right. â”‚
â”‚ -c --center Align to center. â”‚
â”‚ -L --text-left Justify text to left. â”‚
â”‚ -R --text-right Justify text to right. â”‚
â”‚ -C --text-center Justify text to center. â”‚
â”‚ -F --text-full Justify text to both left and right edges. â”‚
â”‚ --soft Enable soft wrapping of text (requires --print). â”‚
â”‚ -e --expand Expand to full width (requires --panel). â”‚
â”‚ -w --width SIZE Fit output to SIZE characters. â”‚
â”‚ -W --max-width SIZE Set maximum width to SIZE characters. â”‚
â”‚ -s --style STYLE Set text style to STYLE. â”‚
â”‚ --rule-style STYLE Set rule style to STYLE. â”‚
â”‚ --rule-char CHARACTER Use CHARACTER to generate a line with --rule. â”‚
â”‚ -d --padding TOP,RIGHT,BOTTOM,LEFT Padding around output. 1, 2 or 4 comma separated integers, e.g. 2,4 â”‚
â”‚ -a --panel BOX Set panel type to BOX. ascii, ascii2, double, heavy, none, rounded, square â”‚
â”‚ -S --panel-style STYLE Set the panel style to STYLE (requires --panel). â”‚
â”‚ --theme THEME Set syntax theme to THEME. See https://pygments.org/styles/ â”‚
â”‚ -n --line-numbers Enable line number in syntax. â”‚
â”‚ -g --guides Enable indentation guides in syntax highlighting â”‚
â”‚ -x --lexer LEXER Use LEXER for syntax highlighting. See https://pygments.org/docs/lexers/ â”‚
â”‚ -y --hyperlinks Render hyperlinks in markdown. â”‚
â”‚ --no-wrap Don't word wrap syntax highlighted files. â”‚
â”‚ --title TEXT Set panel title to TEXT. â”‚
â”‚ --caption TEXT Set panel caption to TEXT. â”‚
â”‚ --force-terminal Force terminal output when not writing to a terminal. â”‚
â”‚ -o --export-html PATH Write HTML to PATH. â”‚
â”‚ --export-svg PATH Write SVG to PATH. â”‚
â”‚ --pager Display in an interactive pager. â”‚
â”‚ -v --version Print version and exit. â”‚
â”‚ --help Show this message and exit. â”‚
